# Privacy-Preserving Clinical RAG System — Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
Companion implementation for the paper "Privacy-Preserving RAG for Clinical Data Systems."
Fully on-premises RAG for clinical/pharmaceutical environments.
ALL data is PUBLIC (PubMed, DrugBank open access, BioASQ). No proprietary data.

## Architecture (6 Layers)
1. Ingestion — Parse PDFs, DOCX, PubMed XML; de-identify PHI at ingest
2. Chunking — Structure-aware chunking preserving clinical document hierarchy
3. Embedding & Indexing — BGE-large-en-v1.5 locally; stored in Qdrant (self-hosted)
4. Hybrid Retrieval — BM25 + dense ANN + cross-encoder reranking with ACL enforcement
5. Local LLM Inference — vLLM serving quantized models (AWQ 4-bit); structured prompting
6. Response Filtering — PHI scanning, hallucination checks, audit logging

## Formal Constraints (C1–C5)
- C1: Every claim in responses must cite retrieved passages
- C2: Retrieval respects user access control lists (ACLs)
- C3: All computation stays within the security perimeter (no external calls)
- C4: Every query/response is audit-logged with full provenance
- C5: System must abstain when evidence is insufficient

## Code Conventions
- Type hints on all functions
- Pydantic models for all data structures with validation constraints
- Dependency injection for swappable backends
- Bearer token auth when ENABLE_AUTH=true
- fcntl file locking on audit logs for multi-worker safety
- No external API calls at runtime
